1046  **********************************************************************
1047  * ELECTRICITY PLANNING MODEL (EPM)
1048  * Developed at the World Bank
1049  **********************************************************************
1050  * Description:
1051  * This GAMS-based model is designed for electricity system planning,
1052  * incorporating capacity expansion, generation dispatch, and policy
1053  * constraints such as renewable energy targets, emissions reductions,
1054  * and market mechanisms.
1055  *
1056  * Author(s): ESMAP Modelling Team
1057  * Organization: World Bank
1058  * Version:
1059  * License: Creative Commons Zero v1.0 Universal
1060  *
1061  * Key Features:
1062  * - Optimization of electricity generation and capacity planning
1063  * - Inclusion of renewable energy integration and storage technologies
1064  * - Multi-period, multi-region modeling framework
1065  * - CO2 emissions constraints and policy instruments
1066  *
1067  * Notes:
1068  * - Ensure GAMS is installed before running this model.
1069  * - The model requires input data in .GDX or Excel format.
1070  *
1071  * Contact:
1072  * Claire Nicolas, cnicolas@worldbank.org
1073  **********************************************************************
1074   
1077   
1078  *-------------------------------------------------------------------
1079  * DECLARATION OF SETS, PARAMETERS AND VARIABLES
1080  *-------------------------------------------------------------------
1081   
1082   
1083   
1084  alias (y,y2);
1085  alias (f,f2);
1086  alias (c,c2);
1087  alias (q,q2);
1088  alias (d,d2);
1089  alias (t,tprev,t2);
1090  alias (AT,AT2);
